    Model structure:
    y = acceleration = 
        p0                              # constant offset
        + p1 * x0                      # linear time dependence (drift or slow variation)
        - |p2| * x1                    # linear restoring force term (-k*x)
        - |p3| * x2                    # linear damping term (-c*v)
        + p4 * (x1 ** 3)              # cubic stiffness nonlinearity
        + p5 * (x2 ** 3)              # cubic nonlinear damping
        + p6 * (x1 ** 2)              # quadratic stiffness nonlinearity
        + p7 * (x2 ** 2)              # quadratic nonlinear damping
        + p8 * (x1 * x2)              # cross term coupling position & velocity
        + p9 * np.sin(x0)             # sinusoidal forcing term (sinusoidal drive)
        + p10* np.cos(x0)             # sinusoidal forcing term (cosine component)
        + p11* ((x1 ** 2) * x2)       # higher order cross nonlinearity

    Additional enhancements:
    - Modulate cubic stiffness by sin(time)
    - Modulate cubic damping by cos(time)
    - Modulate cross product by sin(2*time)
    - Modulate quadratic stiffness by cos(3*time)

