    Models acceleration as a nonlinear function of time (x0), position (x1), and velocity (x2):
    
    y = p0 
        + p1 * x0                      # linear time forcing
        + p2 * x1                      # linear stiffness term
        + p3 * x2                      # linear damping term
        + p4 * x1**3                   # cubic stiffness nonlinearity (Duffing)
        + p5 * (x1**2) * x2            # mixed quadratic position - linear velocity
        + p6 * x1 * (x2**2)            # mixed linear position - quadratic velocity
        + p7 * x2**3                   # cubic velocity nonlinearity (nonlinear damping)
        + p8 * (x0 * x1)               # cross term time-position coupling
