    Models acceleration y as a combination of:
    - constant offset
    - linear and nonlinear restoring forces (position terms)
    - linear and nonlinear damping (velocity terms)
    - coupling between position and velocity
    - sinusoidal forcing with phase shift and amplitude modulation
    - exponential decay/growth modulation on forcing terms
    - friction-like effect modeled smoothly via sign and magnitude of velocity

    Parameters:
        x0: time array
        x1: position array at time t
        x2: velocity array at time t
        params: array-like with length 12

            params[0]: constant offset term
            params[1]: linear position coefficient (restoring force)
            params[2]: cubic position coefficient (Duffing nonlinearity)
            params[3]: linear velocity coefficient (damping)
            params[4]: amplitude of sinusoidal forcing term
            params[5]: frequency multiplier for sinusoidal forcing in time argument
            params[6]: phase shift for sinusoidal forcing / also used in exponential decay rate 
            params[7]: quadratic position coefficient (nonlinear stiffness)
            params[8]: quadratic velocity coefficient (nonlinear damping)
            params[9]: coupling coefficient between position and velocity
            params[10]: amplitude for modulated cosine forcing term 
            params[11]: frequency multiplier for modulated cosine forcing in time argument

    Returns:
